      "id": "opXwRLaAnREnJyZIfhsfA",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1662.3450716522923,
      "y": 198.2893448316957,
      "width": 574.6173858392382,
      "height": 175,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b03",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1351800625,
      "version": 2108,
      "versionNonce": 1284375519,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1783107394937,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "In FWA we can have a fixed time interval\nFor our system to allow reqs for eg 2 reqs/msg per sec.\n\nI.e starting from 0 to 1 sec we will allow user\nTo make 2 reqs to the system, then again allow\n2 more reqs from 1 to 2 sec, preventing our\nSystem from DOS/DDOS Attacks.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "In FWA we can have a fixed time interval\nFor our system to allow reqs for eg 2 reqs/msg per sec.\n\nI.e starting from 0 to 1 sec we will allow user\nTo make 2 reqs to the system, then again allow\n2 more reqs from 1 to 2 sec, preventing our\nSystem from DOS/DDOS Attacks.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Z2ha955vOAs6fLcWylHv6",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2263.901909143148,
      "y": 126.80909525732301,
      "width": 205.2128448486328,
      "height": 35,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b06",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1374891057,
      "version": 244,
      "versionNonce": 197188209,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1783107388217,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "FWA Mechanism",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "FWA Mechanism",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "86uF2INMftt52-JlbFDsp",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2256.3478672254073,
      "y": 177.91136240777496,
      "width": 636.7593383789062,
      "height": 525,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b07",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 35668209,
      "version": 330,
      "versionNonce": 545154129,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1783107388217,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "We can keep track of user & their reqs with hashtable(HT) \nwhere key will be user ID & Value will be the object containing\nfields like timestamp & counter\n\nSo if any user makes req, our rate Limiter first check if user is in\nHT if user is not present, add user in HT with current \nTimestamp & counter=1\n\nIf user is available, check \n\n1) (Current - Previous) Timestamp < 1s\n   counter < threshold limit (2)\n   If true than increment counter\n   & allow req\n\n2) (Current - Previous) Timestamp < 1\n    counter(3) < threshold limit (2)\n   Then reject req with 429 status\n\n3) (Current - Previous) Timestamp > 1s\n   Then reset the counter = 1",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "We can keep track of user & their reqs with hashtable(HT) \nwhere key will be user ID & Value will be the object containing\nfields like timestamp & counter\n\nSo if any user makes req, our rate Limiter first check if user is in\nHT if user is not present, add user in HT with current \nTimestamp & counter=1\n\nIf user is available, check \n\n1) (Current - Previous) Timestamp < 1s\n   counter < threshold limit (2)\n   If true than increment counter\n   & allow req\n\n2) (Current - Previous) Timestamp < 1\n    counter(3) < threshold limit (2)\n   Then reject req with 429 status\n\n3) (Current - Previous) Timestamp > 1s\n   Then reset the counter = 1",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "T93lvgw_AR3jBtUTxeBQz",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1659.3097396167127,
      "y": 149.98606482301227,
      "width": 194.26480102539062,
      "height": 35,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b09",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 868189137,
      "version": 106,
      "versionNonce": 155716991,
      "isDeleted": false,
